T1  - Trade, structure and linkages in Costa Rica: An input-output approach
AU  - Bulmer-Thomas, Victor
JO  - Journal of Development Economics
VL  - 5
IS  - 1
SP  - 73
EP  - 86
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/03/01/
SN  - 0304-3878
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(78)90042-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304387878900421
AB  - Input-output tables for Costa Rica are used first to assess the country's trade performance; it is argued that trade with the rest of Central America has produced a Costa Rican comparative advantage in consumer durables. The paper then uses the input–output tables to examine the economy's structure, which is shown to be block triangular. Finally, measures of linkages are derived from the tables and a critique of the growth-inducing linkage mechanism is presented.
